    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for pacemaker.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 8.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The Pacemaker cluster resource manager is a collection of technologies working together to maintain data integrity and application availability in the event of failures. \n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\n* pacemaker: Pacemaker: Denial of Service via integer overflow in remote message decompression (CVE-2026-10649)\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      },
      {
